summary: House Hardyng is a noble house from the Vale of Arryn. They blazon their arms with a field of red and white diamonds. History...
caption:
House Hardyng is a noble house from the Vale of Arryn. They blazon their arms with a field of red and white diamonds.

History

Ser Humfrey Hardyng participated in the tourney at Ashford Meadow in 209 AC, beginning the tourney as one of the champions. He remained a champion, even after Prince Aerion Targaryen killed his horse. Humfrey took Ser Duncan the Tall’s side in the trial of seven. He was severely injured and later died of his wounds.

summary: Book foreshadowings hinting at Tyrion loosing his tongue ?
body:
Book foreshadowings hinting at Tyrion loosing his tongue ?

I see this theory being discussed since a few days by my mutuals on twitter, that maybe Tyrion could have his tongue cut in s8, so I’ve been curious and I decided to check the books. I entered “Tyrion” + “tongue” in asearchoficeandfire and it been interesting. Most of the results were people telling Tyrion he had a bold tongue, or Tyrion having to bit his tongue or hold his tongue back not to say certain things to certain persons… And there were also those the three following quotes :

(A Clash of Kings - Tyrion III) “A folly,” sighed Tyrion. “When you tear out a man's tongue, you are not proving him a liar, you’re only telling the world that you fear what he might say.”

(A Storm of Swords - Sansa III) “I did, Your Grace,” said Tyrion, “but only because I envied your royal manhood. Mine own is so small and stunted.” His face twisted into a leer. “And if you take my tongue, you will leave me no way at all to pleasure this sweet wife you gave me.”

(A Storm of Swords - Tyrion VI) “You have a certain cunning, Tyrion, but the plain truth is you talk too much. That loose tongue of yours will be your undoing.”

Thoughts ?

summary: D*ny's stans become a little bit desperate lately and I honestly don't understand the reason. In their picture Sansa is either...
question: D*ny's stans become a little bit desperate lately and I honestly don't understand the reason. In their picture Sansa is either the evil manipulative bitch who betrays her poor innocent Jonny or irrelevant stupid little girl who is good for nothing. Why do they need the character who no one cares about or hate? I thought Arya as queen's beloved sister is pretty much canon. What this annoying obsession with Sansa, her hair, her sewing skills, her chamber is about? I truly don't understand
answer: They’re threatened, not just by the Jonsa fandom but also the fact that Sansa is a main character whose allegiance to the Starks (the protagonists, the Good Side) is solid and whose importance has been affirmed by actors and directors. So they’re caught between pretending they want Sansa as Dany’s ‘sister’ and wishing terrible things on her.

summary: Sansa is very reserved person and obviously not a type of person who's going to chat about her past with the stranger. She would...
question: Sansa is very reserved person and obviously not a type of person who's going to chat about her past with the stranger. She would need time, too much time to open herself to another human being. And I don't think Daenerys will stay in winterfell for a long time, she probably will leave pretty soon. So I don't this their relationship be more than cold politeness (at least from Sansa, Daenerys has a temper, she'll do smth terrible in the north I'm sure)
answer: Exactly. Dany stans think Sansa will warm up to Dany immediately and start sprouting off private information that Sansa refused to share with Arya (you know when Sansa said she survived a lot of terrible things and then said nothing more about the subject). They think of Sansa as prop more than a main character and it’s extremely frustrating because they come into Sansa’s tag pretending they’re being benevolent when they push something like this.
